Business Brief -- Trans Financial Bancorp Inc.:
   Company Backs Rights Plan
   To Deter Hostile Takeover
The rights can be exercised after any person or group
acquires 15% or more of the company's outstanding stock, or
if "disinterested" directors designate a person or group with
more than 10% ownership as being adverse to the company. The
rights also can be exercised if a tender offer is announced
for 25% or more of the company's common stock outstanding.